[Client lifetime](https://devblogs.microsoft.com/azure-sdk/lifetime-management-and-thread-safety-guarantees-of-azure-sdk-net-clients/)

## Examples

### Authenticate the client and get the workspace collection

```C# Snippet:DefenderEasmSample_AuthenticateAndGetCollection
TokenCredential cred = new DefaultAzureCredential();
ArmClient client = new ArmClient(cred);

string subscriptionId = "<your-subscription-id>";
string resourceGroupName = "<your-resource-group>";
ResourceIdentifier resourceGroupResourceId = ResourceGroupResource.CreateResourceIdentifier(subscriptionId, resourceGroupName);
ResourceGroupResource resourceGroupResource = client.GetResourceGroupResource(resourceGroupResourceId);

EasmWorkspaceCollection workspaces = resourceGroupResource.GetEasmWorkspaces();
```

### Create or update a workspace

```C# Snippet:DefenderEasmSample_CreateWorkspace
EasmWorkspaceData data = new EasmWorkspaceData(new AzureLocation("eastus"));
ArmOperation<EasmWorkspaceResource> lro = await workspaces.CreateOrUpdateAsync(WaitUntil.Completed, "my-easm-workspace", data);
EasmWorkspaceResource workspace = lro.Value;
Console.WriteLine($"Created workspace: {workspace.Data.Name}");
```

### List all workspaces in a resource group

```C# Snippet:DefenderEasmSample_ListWorkspaces
await foreach (EasmWorkspaceResource workspace in workspaces.GetAllAsync())
{
    Console.WriteLine($"Workspace: {workspace.Data.Name} in {workspace.Data.Location}");
}
```

### Create a label

```C# Snippet:DefenderEasmSample_CreateLabel
EasmLabelCollection labels = workspace.GetEasmLabels();
EasmLabelData labelData = new EasmLabelData();
ArmOperation<EasmLabelResource> labelLro = await labels.CreateOrUpdateAsync(WaitUntil.Completed, "my-label", labelData);
EasmLabelResource label = labelLro.Value;
Console.WriteLine($"Created label: {label.Data.Name}");
```

For more code examples, see [Azure.ResourceManager.DefenderEasm samples](https://github.com/Azure/azure-sdk-for-net/tree/main/sdk/defendereasm/Azure.ResourceManager.DefenderEasm/tests/Generated/Samples).
```

Also update the `### Authenticate the Client` section (under Getting started) to add a code sample:

